President Donald Trump will meet with Prince Salman bin Hamad Al-Khalifa, the Crown Prince of Bahrain, at the White House on September 16, 2019. The purpose of the meeting is to strengthen the strategic partnership and friendship between the United States and Bahrain, as well as enhance economic and security cooperation. The two leaders will discuss topics such as maritime security, countering the threat from Iran, efforts to promote peace in the region, and counterterrorism.